{"id":26170,"date":"2020-11-12T22:59:29","date_gmt":"2020-11-12T22:59:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/?page_id=26170"},"modified":"2023-12-04T20:28:48","modified_gmt":"2023-12-04T20:28:48","slug":"fellowship","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/fellowship\/","title":{"rendered":"Fellowship"},"content":{"rendered":"\n\n\t<h1><strong>CONGRESSIONAL POLICY FELLOWSHIP<\/strong><\/h1>\n\t<p>The application for ISF&#8217;s Congressional Policy Fellowship is now open!<\/p>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.submittable.com\/submit\/270224\/2023-isf-congressional-policy-fellowship\/eligibility\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tApply Now\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t<p>The ISF Congressional Policy Fellowship is a 9-month, full-time program that provides fellows with an opportunity to work in Washington D.C. on legislative and public policy issues at Congressional offices.<\/p>\n<p><strong>This opportunity is for American Muslims who are committed to a career in public service.<\/strong><\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\tAbout the Program\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The ISF Congressional Policy Fellowship is a highly selective, nonpartisan program devoted to promoting and encouraging diversity and inclusion on Capitol Hill.\u00a0 Through a 9 month fellowship, fellows will gain real-world experience working on legislative and public policy issues.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/IMG_0131.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_0131\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1536\" width=\"2049\" title=\"IMG_0131\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/20413916_10213654334540782_1196259562507798748_o-2.jpg\" alt=\"20413916_10213654334540782_1196259562507798748_o-2\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"810\" width=\"1080\" title=\"20413916_10213654334540782_1196259562507798748_o-2\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tWhat to Expect\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Fellows of this program will not only have access to Congressional members and staff within the halls of power, they will have the opportunity to work as a full-time staffer for 9 months conducting tasks such as policy research, meeting with special interest groups, drafting bills\/speeches, and preparing the member for hearings, etc.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\tCommitment\n\t<\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Upon arrival in D.C., participants will attend a one-day preparatory orientation. Typically fellows will work 40-45 hours a week and will be expected to participate in all ISF-sponsored activities including professional development events. As participants will be representing ISF, they should work to meet ISF&#8217;s work performance and ethics.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/islamicscholarshipfund.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/AdobeStock_211208954-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Female speaker giving a talk on corporate Business Conference. Audience at the conference hall. Business and Entrepreneurship event.\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1315\" width=\"2560\" title=\"Public speaker giving talk at Business Event.\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\"  \/>\n\t\n<em>Applications are evaluated based on evidence of leadership potential and professional skills to succeed in a public service position.<\/em>\n\n<h3>\n\t\tEligibility\n\t<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Muslim;<\/li>\n<li>Graduated with an undergraduate or graduate degree from an accredited university;<\/li>\n<li>A U.S. citizen, permanent resident of the United States or a DACA recipient<\/li>\n<li>Minimum of one year of full-time professional experience in the field of policy. Two to three years of experience is preferred.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Applicants should have a proven commitment to a career in policy-making and public service.<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>\n\t\tRequirements\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<ul>\n<li>Application form<\/li>\n<li>Resume<\/li>\n<li>Cover Letter<\/li>\n<li>Video introduction<\/li>\n<li>Essay Questions<\/li>\n<li>College transcripts<\/li>\n<li>Policy interests<\/li>\n<li>Two letters of recommendation<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3>\n\t\tFellowship Benefits\n\t<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Salary of $35,000 for housing and other expenses for the 9-month fellowship.<\/li>\n<li>Roundtrip Airfare to D.C.<\/li>\n<li>Health insurance reimbursement up to $200 a month<\/li>\n<li>Placement in a congressional office<\/li>\n<li>One-day Hill orientation<\/li>\n<li>Professional leadership and policy enrichment\u00a0workshops throughout the program<\/li>\n<li>Networking opportunities<\/li>\n<li>Mentorship throughout the program and access to our online mentorship platform<\/li>\n<li>Support with job placement after program<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>\n\t\tProgram Timeline\n\t<\/h2>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Applications<\/h4><p>ISF will start accepting online applications in August.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Deadline<\/h4><p>The deadline to apply for the fellowship is in October.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Acceptance<\/h4><p>After applying, selected candidates will be given a conditional acceptance by ISF, and ISF will use its Congressional connections to help candidates get a position in a Congressional office.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Interviews<\/h4><p>Candidates will interview with offices. Once an office extends an offer to a candidate, a final acceptance will automatically be given to candidates by ISF.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Fellowship Starts<\/h4><p>Fellowships will begin in D.C. in January. Fellows will work full-time hours with Congressional offices (as set by the office) starting in September and are not permitted to have any other internships or employment.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Sessions &#038; Workshops<\/h4><p>Fellows are required to attend ISF- hosted sessions and workshops throughout their time in D.C.<\/p><\/li><li>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t<h4>Exit Interview<\/h4><p>Fellows end their position in September with an exit interview and can continue to receive mentorship support for permanent job placement .<\/p><\/li>\t<\/ul>\n<h3>\n\t\tFAQS\n\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-0\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\">How many Fellows are selected?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-0\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-0\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>1-2 Fellows will be selected.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-1\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\">How much is the fellowship salary?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-1\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-1\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>The salary for Fellows is $35,000 over 9 months, plus insurance benefits.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-2\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\">Does the fellowship pay for housing?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-2\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-2\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>No, it does not cover housing.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"fl-accordion--label-3\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-3\">Can I work a part-time job during the fellowship?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#\" id=\"fl-accordion--icon-3\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"fl-accordion--panel-3\"><i>Expand<\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>It is highly discouraged to take on part-time work during your Congressional Fellowship. We advise all applicants to plan to make the most of their time working in a Congressional office and on Capitol Hill.<\/p>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>CONGRESSIONAL POLICY FELLOWSHIP The application for ISF&#821